basicCard.title: HDHP
basicCard.formattedText:
High Deductible Health Plan, for the insurer, a higher deductible means you are responsible for a greater amount of your initial health care costs, saving them money. For you, the benefit comes in lower monthly premiums. If you have a high-deductible plan, you are eligible for a Health Savings Account.
 
    
You can also ask about:    
   Out-of-Network Provider    
   Coinsurance    
   PPO    
  
Would you like a journey to Manage your Health, Manage your Money, or a journey for those New to Insurance
